er%20using%20a%20no-down%20payment%20loan%20backed%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Veterans%20Affairs.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20born%20in%20Minnesota%20and%20lived%20there%20until%20I%20joined%20the%20Marine%20Corps%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20growing%20up%2C%20my%20family%20never%20owned%20a%20home%20%E2%80%94%20we%20lived%20in%20trailer%20parks%20and%20duplexes.%20I%20was%20always%20moving%20and%20I%20never%20felt%20like%20I%20had%20a%20place%20of%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20became%20a%20mother%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20a%20homeowner%20so%20I%20could%20ensure%20that%20my%20son%20%E2%80%94%20who%20has%20high-functioning%20autism%20%E2%80%94%20had%20a%20better%20childhood%20than%20mine.%20The%20road%20to%20homeownership%20wasn't%20easy.%20I%20have%20made%20many%20sacrifices%20along%20the%20way%20but%20being%20able%20to%20give%20my%20child%20a%20sense%20of%20security%20is%20worth%20it%20all.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaving%20for%20a%20home%20purchase%20was%20tough%20as%20a%20single%20mother%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20I%20began%20my%20home%20buying%20journey.%20I%20was%20working%20for%20the%20US%20government%20and%20receiving%20additional%20money%20from%20the%20Department%20of%20Veteran%20Affairs%20for%20a%20disability.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20I%20had%20managed%20to%20save%20up%20%243%2C000%20for%20a%20down%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20I%20was%20living%20in%20a%20quaint%201%2C100%20square-foot%20home%20in%20Austin%2C%20Texas%2C%20that%20cost%20%241%2C800%20a%20month.%20It%20was%20a%20good%20temporary%20home%20but%20it%20just%20wasn't%20for%20us%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20I%20knew%20I%20could%20do%20better.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20going%20to%20continue%20renting%20in%20Austin%20while%20I%20saved%20up%20more%20money%20for%20a%20home%20purchase.%20However%2C%20housing%20prices%20were%20getting%20increasingly%20higher%20in%20the%20area.%20The%20population%20in%20the%20neighborhood%20where%20my%20son%20and%20I%20lived%20had%20grown%20dramatically%20and%20the%20homes%20and%20apartments%20were%20becoming%20overpriced.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20rent%20increased%20by%20%24100%20a%20month%20during%20this%20time%20period%2C%20which%20made%20it%20even%20more%20difficult%20for%20me%2C%20as%20a%20single%20mother%2C%20to%20pay%20for%20housing%2C%20provide%20for%20my%20son%2C%20and%20budget%20for%20a%20home%20purchase.%20Every%20time%20I%20felt%20like%20I%20was%20getting%20ahead%2C%20something%20came%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20began%20to%20feel%20stuck%20where%20I%20lived.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFinding%20the%20right%20home%20comes%20with%20ups%20and%20downs%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20April%2C%20I%20decided%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20leave%20the%20Austin%20area%20and%20began%20looking%20for%20homes%20in%20Houston%2C%20a%20market%20I%20heard%20was%20reasonably%20priced%20but%20also%20had%20good%20schools%20for%20children%20with%20autism.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20month%2C%20I%20found%20a%20four-bedroom%2C%20three-and-a-half%20bathroom%20home%20listed%20online%20for%20%24568%2C000.%20I%20put%20an%20offer%20on%20the%20home%20and%20it%20was%20accepted%20by%20the%20owners.%20However%2C%20three%20days%20before%20closing%20an%20appraiser%20with%20the%20Veterans%20Affairs%20inspected%20the%20home%20and%20informed%20me%20that%20its%20asking%20price%20was%20%24105%2C000%20more%20than%20what%20the%20home%20was%20actually%20worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20situation%20made%20me%20realize%20just%20how%20competitive%20the%20housing%20market%20was%20in%20Houston%20%E2%80%94%20it%20also%20made%20me%20want%20to%20give%20up%20on%20buying%20a%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20made%20a%20post%20in%20a%20Facebook%20first-time%20homebuyers%20group%20explaining%20how%20discouraged%20I%20felt%20about%20the%20process.%20A%20friend%20of%20mine%20encouraged%20me%20to%20start%20looking%20for%20homes%20in%20the%20Dallas%20area.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20two%20days%20after%20the%20home%20in%20Houston%20fell%20through%2C%20I%20found%20a%20new%20real%20estate%20agent%20in%20Dallas%20who%20helped%20me%20find%20an%20affordable%20three-bedroom%2C%20two-bathroom%20home%20that%20was%20listed%20below%20my%20budget%20of%20%24680%2C000.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20living%20three%20hours%20away%20in%20Austin%2C%20so%20I%20couldn't%20physically%20see%20the%20home.%20Although%20I%20only%20saw%20photos%20and%20FaceTime%20videos%20of%20the%20property%2C%20I%20put%20in%20an%20offer.%20It%20was%20accepted%20immediately%20and%20I%20went%20on%20to%20purchase%20the%20house%20with%20a%20VA%20home%20loan%20for%20a%20little%20bit%20under%20%24500%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20able%20to%20afford%20the%20purchase%20with%20the%20money%20I%20saved%20up%2C%C2%A0%20in%20addition%20to%20funds%20I%20received%20from%20streaming%20online%20in%20my%20free%20time.%20I%20also%20sold%20things%20I%20thought%20I%20could%20purchase%20later%20like%20furniture%2C%20clothes%2C%C2%A0%20and%20electronics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20broke%20away%20from%20the%20cycle%20of%20renting%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20have%20three%20adult%20brothers%20and%20one%20sister%2C%20but%20only%20two%20of%20us%20own%20homes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20thinking%20the%20American%20dream%20of%20homeownership%20was%20about%20a%20white%20picket%20fence%2C%20a%20nice%20house%2C%20and%20a%20big%20green%20yard%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0%20but%20that's%20not%20the%20case.%20It's%20about%20all%20the%20steps%20you%20take%20in%20between%20to%20find%20the%20right%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20it's%20become%20extremely%20difficult%20to%20achieve%20homeownership%20in%20the%20United%20States%20it%20is%20still%20possible.%20I%20was%20scared%20during%20my%20home%20buying%20journey%2C%20and%20there%20were%20times%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20give%20up%20but%20I%20persisted.%20That%20is%20a%20big%20