%243%20billion%20bailout%20programme%20for%20Pakistan%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20lender%20said%2C%20which%20will%20immediately%20disburse%20about%20%241.2%20billion%20to%20help%20the%20South%20Asian%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fimf-approves-3-billion-bailout-for-pakistan-4202047%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fimf-approves-3-billion-bailout-for-pakistan-4202047%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fimf-approves-3-billion-bailout-for-pakistan-4202047%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Bahubali%20Rocket'%2C%20With%20100%25%20Success%20Rate%2C%20To%20Send%20Chandrayaan-3%20To%20Moon%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIndia's%20upgraded%20'Bahubali'%20rocket%20is%20standing%20tall%20on%20the%20coast%20of%20the%20Bay%20of%20Bengal%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh's%20Sriharikota%20waiting%20to%20loft%20India's%20Chandrayaan-3%20satellite%20towards%20the%20moon.%20It%20is%20an%20important%20experiment%20to%20master%20soft%20landing%20on%20a%20celestial%20body%20and%20if%20all%20goes%20well%20then%20the%20third%20lunar%20journey%20by%20India%20will%20begin%20on%20Friday%20(July%2014)%20at%202.35%20pm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Indian%20folklore%2C%20the%20moon%20is%20often%20referred%20to%20as%20'%3Cem%3Echanda%20mama%3C%2Fem%3E'%20-%20the%20loving%20uncle%20and%20in%20other%20cultures%2C%20Artemis%20is%20personification%20of%20the%20moon%20as%20a%20female%20goddess.%20Mission%20Chandrayaan%20is%20India's%20indigenous%20effort%20to%20access%20moon%2C%20Artemis%20Program%20is%20America's%20effort%20to%20go%20back%20to%20the%20moon%20in%20the%2021st%20century.%20It%20may%20come%20as%20a%20surprise%20but%20India's%20Chandrayaan-1%20in%202008%2C%20it%20seems%2C%20stirred%20the%20US%20from%20its%20almost%2050%20year%20lunar%20slumber%2C%20and%20the%20ambitious%20Artemis%20Program%20was%20born%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%20is%20India's%20third%20mission%20to%20the%20moon%20and%20a%20satellite%20weighing%203921%20kilograms%20will%20be%20lofted%20on%20its%20long%2C%20nearly%20four%20lakh%20kilometre%2C%20journey.%20The%20upgraded%20'Bahubali'%20rocket%2C%20now%20renamed%20Launch%20Vehicle%20Mark%203%20(LM-3)%2C%20weighs%20642%20tons%2C%20which%20is%20equal%20to%20the%20combined%20weight%20of%20about%20130%20full%20grown%20Asian%20elephants.%20It%20is%20a%20humongous%20rocket%20standing%2043.5%20meters%20tall%2C%20which%20is%20more%20than%20half%20the%20height%20of%20the%20Qutub%20Minar%20which%20is%2072%20meters%20tall.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20will%20be%20the%20sixth%20flight%20of%20the%20rocket%20which%20has%20a%20one%20hundred%20per%20cent%20success%20rate%20till%20datw.%20Hence%2C%20hopes%20are%20high%20for%20the%20successful%20lift%20off%20from%20India's%20space%20port.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChandrayaan-3%20is%20essentially%20a%20bold%20scientific%20mission%20with%20an%20objective%20to%20successfully%20demonstrate%20soft%20landing%20near%20the%20south%20pole%20of%20the%20moon.%20It%20also%20carries%20seven%20scientific%20instruments%2C%20if%20India%20succeeds%20it%20will%20become%20the%20fourth%20country%20after%20Russia%2C%20USA%20and%20China%20to%20soft%20land%20on%20the%20moon%2C%20said%20Mr%20S%20Somanath%2C%20Chairman%2C%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SUV%20sized%20satellite%20is%20essentially%20a%20large%20propulsion%20module%20which%20will%20nudge%20the%20Vikram%20Lander%20and%20Pragyaan%20Rover%20to%20the%20lunar%20orbit.%20If%20all%20goes%20as%20per%20the%20plan%2C%20the%20earliest%20the%20lunar%20landing%20could%20be%20attempted%20will%20be%20on%20August%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20hopes%20to%20carry%20out%20analysis%20of%20the%20lunar%20soil%2C%20rove%20around%20the%20moon%20surface%2C%20also%20log%20moon%20quakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMore%20importantly%2C%20if%20Chandrayaan-3%20succeeds%2C%20we%20may%20see%20the%20first%20Indian%20selfies%20from%20the%20lunar%20surface%20showing%20India's%20flag%20on%20the%20moon%20surface%20since%20both%20the%20Indian%20robots%20Vikram%20and%20Pragyaan%20carry%20imprints%20of%20India's%20tricolour.%20Both%20have%20suitably%20placed%20cameras%20in%20this%20new%20era%20of%20social%20media.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20first%20attempted%20a%20mission%20to%20the%20moon%20in%202008%20with%20Chandrayaan-1%20which%20was%20an%20orbiter%2C%20it%20died%20about%20half%20way%20into%20the%20mission%20but%20it%20came%20back%20with%20the%20globally%20startling%20finding%20that%20the%20moon%20is%20not%20a%20parched%20desert.%20Chandrayaan-1%20discovered%20the%20presence%20of%20water%20molecules%20on%20the%20moon.%20It%20changed%20the%20geological%20history%20of%20the%20moon%20once%20and%20for%20all%20and%20has%20opened%20up%20the%20tantalizing%20possibility%20of%20human%20habitation%20outside%20the%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20this%20finding%20which%20made%20the%20US%20and%20NASA%20wake%20up%20from%20their%20nearly%20fifty-year-old%20lunar%20slumber.%20Chandrayaan-1%20was%20also%20a%20mission%20imprinted%20with%20national%20pride%2C%20here%20India%20was%20the%20captain%20and%20all%20others%20-%20US%2C%20Great%20Britain%20and%20the%20European%20Space%20Agency%20-%20were%20players%20as%20India%20exited%20the%20embrace%20of%20the%20Earth's%20gravity%20for%20the%20first%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202019%2C%20as%20a%20follow%20up%20mission%2C%20India%20attempted%20Chandrayaan-2.%20Here%20an%20orbiter%2C%20a%20lander%20and%20rover%20were%20lofted%20to%20the%20moon.%20The%20Chandrayaan-2%20orbiter%20is%20an%20unmitigated%20success%20and%20continues%20to%20successfully%20orbit%20the%20moon.%20Unfortunately%20the%20Vikram%20lander%20with%20the%20Pragyaan%20rover%20in%20its%20womb%20crash%20landed%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface%20minutes%20before%20it%20was%20to%20touchdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20M%20Annadurai%2C%20the%20then%20head%20of%20the%20Chandrayaan%20program%20at%20ISRO%20said%20an%20under-tested%20machine%20was%20sent%20to%20the%20moon%20and%20one%20big%20reason%20attributed%20to%20the%20failure%20is%20the%20late%20introduction%20of%20the%20fifth%20engine%20on%20the%20lander.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20were%20also%20software%20glitches%20in%20the%20navigation%20and%20approach%20autonomous%20computer%20programs.%20Mr%20Somanath%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20confidence%20level%20for%20soft%20landing%20is%20very%20high%20as%20Vikram%20lander%20has%20been%20made%20more%20robust%20and%20several%20of%20the%20parameters%20that%20could%20lead%20to%20failure%20have%20been%20suitably%20addressed%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Annadurai%20said%20in%20Chandrayaan-2%2C%20the%20Vikram%20lander%20did%20not%20undergo%20rigorous%20%26quot%3Bhot%20testing%20through%20real%20simulations%26quot%3B.%20Mr%20Somanath%20said%20several%20test%20beds%20were%20created%20simulating%20the%20lunar%20surface%20and%20all%20%26quot%3Bknown%20unknowns%20have%20been%20addressed%26quot%3B%20but%20he%20cautions%20it%20still%20remains%20%26quot%3Brocket%20science%26quot%3B%20which%20has%20its%20inherent%20risks%20but%20confirms%20that%20the%20fifth%20middle%20engine%20has%20been%20jettisoned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20India's%20soft%20lander%20crashed%20in%202019%2C%20Israel%20and%20Japan%20also%20attempted%20similar%20soft%20landings%20which%20ended%20in%20disappointments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20summit%20meeting%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Joe%20Biden%20in%20Washington%2C%20India%20recently%20inked%20the%20Artemis%20Accords%20which%20are%20a%20set%20of%20non-binding%20regulations%20spearheaded%20by%20NASA%20as%20it%20embarks%20on%20its%20billions%20of%20dollar%20Artemis%20Program%20to%20send%20the%20first%20lady%20to%20the%20moon%20in%20over%20a%20year%20from%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BArtemis%20Accords%20are%20good%20for%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20India's%20'moon%20man'%20Dr%20Mylswamy%20Annadurai%2C%20who%20piloted%20India%20to%20moon%20and%20Mars%20from%20ISRO.%20He%20asserted%2C%20%26quot%3BIndia's%20signing%20of%20the%20Artemis%20Accords%20to%20partner%20in%20exploration%20of%20moon%20and%20Mars%20along%20with%20the%20US%20and%20others%20is%20a%20good%20step%20forward%26quot%3B%2C%20adding%20international%20collaborative%20lunar%20exploration%20can't%20happen%20without%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia's%20flag%20is%20already%20on%20the%20South%20Pole%20of%20the%20moon%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dr%20Annadurai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20consequence%2C%20Dr%20Annadurai%20said%2C%20it%20was%20India's%20frugal%2C%20below%20%24100%20million%2C%20moon%20mission%20which%20opened%20the%20eyes%20of%20NASA%20that%20had%20almost%20forgotten%20about%20the%20moon%20since%201972.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESharing%20the%20excitement%2C%20Professor%20Carle%20Pieters%2C%20from%20the%20Brown%20University%2C%20US%20-%20the%20principal%20scientist%20credited%20for%20discovering%20the%20presence%20of%20water%20molecules%20on%20the%20moon%20surface%20using%20data%20provided%20by%20instruments%20flown%20on%20Chandrayaan-1%20-%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThese%20are%20exciting%20times.%20The%20growing%20international%20science%20and%20exploration%20community%20recognises%20the%20moon%20has%20been%20our%20constant%20companion%20in%20this%20part%20of%20the%20solar%20system%20and%20always%20will%20be.%20I%20am%20sure%20the%20engineers%2C%20scientists%2C%20and%20students%20across%20India%2C%20ISRO%20who%20have%20dedicated%20their%20hearts%20and%20minds%20to%20move%20Chandrayaan-3%20forward%20will%20be%20rewarded%20with%20new%20knowledge%20and%20understanding.%20I%20hope%20any%20surprises%20will%20be%20good%20ones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689183060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2F83cp1tf8_chandrayaan3_625x300_11_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F