20continues%2C%20the%20%5BS%26amp%3BP%20500%5D%20may%20be%20mostly%20flat%20over%20the%20next%20three%20months%20until%20it%20anniversaries%20its%20October%202022%20low.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-new-bull-rally-economy-employment-upside-ahead-2023-6%5C%22%3Estock%20market's%20current%20bull%20rally%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20likely%20to%20be%20of%20the%20slow-and-steady%20variety%20if%20history%20is%20a%20guide%2C%20and%20that%20means%20sluggish%20gains%20ahead%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Wednesday%20note%20from%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatatrekresearch.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDataTrek%20Research.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20research%20firm%20compared%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fstock-market-outlook-new-bull-rally-economy-employment-upside-ahead-2023-6%5C%22%3Ethe%20current%20stock%20market%20surge%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20four%20prior%20bull%20market%20cycles%20that%20began%20in%201990%2C%202002%2C%202009%2C%20and%202020%2C%20and%20found%20that%20there%20are%20two%20types%20of%20rallies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20type%20is%20a%20high-octane%20rally%2C%20like%20was%20seen%20in%20the%202009%20and%202020%20bull%20markets%20when%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fs%26amp%3Bp_500%5C%22%3ES%26amp%3BP%20500%3C%2Fa%3E%20surged%20more%20than%2060%25%20after%20185%20trading%20days%20from%20its%20bottom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20type%20is%20slow-and-steady%2C%20like%20was%20seen%20in%20the%201990%20and%202002%20bull%20markets%20when%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%C2%A0%20500%20jumped%20about%2030%25%20after%20185%20trading%20days%20from%20its%20bottom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20having%20bottomed%20in%20mid-October%2C%20or%20185%20trading%20days%20ago%2C%20it%20has%20since%20rallied%2024%25%2C%20putting%20it%20in%20the%20slow-and-steady%20category%2C%20according%20to%20DataTrek%20co-founder%20Jessica%20Rabe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221423%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22S%26amp%3BP%20500%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aed8b494be880019f39fd3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22835%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDataTrek%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20that%20analog%20continues%2C%20the%20index%20may%20be%20mostly%20flat%20over%20the%20next%20three%20months%20until%20it%20anniversaries%20its%20October%202022%20low.%20The%20S%26amp%3BP%20only%20gained%201.3%25%20over%20the%20next%2066%20trading%20days%20from%20today%20when%20taking%20the%20average%20of%20our%201990%20-%201991%20and%202002%20-%202003%20comparisons%2C%26quot%3B%20Rabe%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20similar%20story%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Findex%2Fnasdaq_composite%5C%22%3ENasdaq%20Composite%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20up%20about%2035%25%20since%20its%20bear%20market%20low.%20Rabe%20highlighted%20that%20the%20gain%20is%20closer%20to%20the%201990%20and%202002%20bull%20markets%20than%20the%202009%20and%202020%20bull%20markets%2C%20which%20saw%20gains%20of%20more%20than%2060%25%20this%20far%20removed%20from%20the%20bottom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20Nasdaq%20follows%20the%20same%20pattern%20of%20the%201990%20and%202002%20bull%20markets%2C%20as%20it%20has%20so%20far%2C%20it%20could%20see%20gains%20of%20about%208%25%20over%20the%20next%20three%20months%20and%20gains%20of%2018%25%20over%20the%20next%20six%20months.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221363%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Nasdaq%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64aed8e78ed31300199ea741%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22817%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDataTrek%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp