ed%20by%20economists.%20Month%20over%20month%2C%20the%20gauge%20climbed%200.2%25%2C%20less%20than%20the%200.3%25%20expected%2C%20according%20to%20the%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics.%20The%20year-over-year%20reading%20is%20the%20lowest%20since%20March%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20fed%20fund%20futures%2C%20markets%20think%20this%20month%20is%20the%20last%20hurrah%20for%20the%20central%20bank's%20rate-hike%20campaign.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInvestors%20expect%20the%20central%20bank%20to%20raise%20its%20benchmark%20rate%20by%2025%20basis%20points%20to%20a%20range%20of%205.25%25-5.50%25%20this%20month%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cmegroup.com%2Fmarkets%2Finterest-rates%2Fcme-fedwatch-tool.html%3Fredirect%3D%2Ftrading%2Finterest-rates%2Fcountdown-to-fomc.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECME's%20FedWatch%20Tool%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20midday%20Wednesday%2C%20traders%20saw%2092%25%20odds%20of%20quarter-point%20hike%20at%20the%20July%2025-26%20meeting%2C%20with%20the%20highest%20odds%20in%20the%20months%20following%20indicating%20investors%20think%20the%20Fed%20will%20hold%20off%20on%20more%20increases%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20this%20year.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStocks%20jumped%20after%20the%20release%2C%20with%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20climbing%20roughly%201%25%2C%20the%20Nasdaq%20moving%20up%201.2%25%2C%20and%20the%20Dow%20ticking%20about%200.82%25%20higher.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBond%20yields%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20tumbled.%20The%2010-year%20yield%20moved%20six%20basis%20points%20lower%2C%20reversing%20last%20week's%20surge%2C%20in%20a%20sign%20that%20investors%20are%20getting%20more%20upbeat%20about%20what's%20to%20come%20and%20placing%20bets%20that%20rates%20don't%20have%20much%20further%20to%20rise.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20market's%20optimism%20that%20Jerome%20Powell%20and%20his%20colleagues%20are%20nearly%20done%20tightening%20monetary%20policy%20runs%20counter%20to%20comment