e.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20driving%20a%20Ferrari%20for%20a%20month%20then%20suddenly%20it%20turns%20into%20a%20beaten%20up%20old%20pickup.%20I'm%20not%20sure%20I%20want%20to%20pay%20for%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeter%20Yang%2C%20a%20product%20lead%20at%20Roblox%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fpetergyang%2Fstatus%2F1660314935208054785%5C%22%3Etweeted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20model%20was%20generating%20faster%20outputs%20but%20the%20quality%20was%20worse.%20%26quot%3BJust%20simple%20questions%20like%20making%20writing%20more%20clear%20and%20concise%20and%20generating%20ideas%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%20%26quot%3BThe%20writing%20quality%20has%20gone%20down%20in%20my%20opinion.%26quot%3B%20He%20asked%20if%20anyone%20else%20had%20noticed%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20found%20it%20to%20be%20lazier%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20user%2C%20Frazier%20MacLeod%2C%20replied.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChristi%20Kennedy%20wrote%20on%20OpenAI's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommunity.openai.com%2Ft%2Fexperiencing-decreased-performance-with-chatgpt-4%2F234269%2F77%5C%22%3Edeveloper%20forum%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20GPT-4%20had%20started%20looping%20outputs%20of%20code%20and%20other%20information%20over%20and%20over%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20braindead%20vs.%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommunity.openai.com%2Ft%2Fexperiencing-decreased-performance-with-chatgpt-4%2F234269%2F78%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20month.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20aren't%20actually%20pushing%20it%20with%20what%20it%20could%20do%20previously%2C%20you%20wouldn't%20notice.%20Yet%20if%20you%20are%20really%20using%20it%20fully%2C%20you%20see%20it%20is%20obviously%20much%20dumber.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFrom%20slow%20and%20expensive%2C%20to%20fast%20and%20inaccurate%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20quite%20a%20change%20from%20earlier%20this%20year%20when%20OpenAI%20was%20wowing%20the%20world%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feverything-you-need-to-know-about-chat-gpt-2023-1%5C%22%3EChatGPT%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20tech%20industry%20awaited%20the%20launch%20of%20GPT-4%20with%20rapt%20anticipation.%20ChatGPT%20originally%20ran%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt-3-language-generation-model-important-breakthrough-2020-7%5C%22%3EGPT-3%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20GPT-3.5.%20These%20are%20the%20giant%2C%20underlying%20AI%20models%20that%20power%20its%20uncanny%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20larger%20GPT-4%20was%20launched%20in%20March%20and%20quickly%20became%20the%20go-to%20model%20for%20developers%20and%20other%20tech%20industry%20insiders.%20It's%20considered%20the%20most-powerful%20AI%20model%20available%20broadly%20and%20is%20multimodal%2C%20which%20means%20it%20can%20understand%20images%20as%20well%20as%20text%20inputs.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20initial%20rush%20to%20try%20out%20this%20new%20model%2C%20some%20were%20shocked%20by%20their%20bills%20for%20using%20GPT-4.%20It%20was%20slow%20but%20very%20accurate%2C%20according%20to%20Sharon%20Zhou%2C%20CEO%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lamini.ai%5C%22%3ELamini%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20startup%20that%20helps%20developers%20build%20custom%20large%20language%20models.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20Ship%20of%20Theseus%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20the%20situation%20until%20a%20few%20weeks%20ago.%20Then%20GPT-4%20got%20quicker%2C%20but%20the%20performance%20noticeably%20waned%2C%20fueling%20talk%20across%20the%20AI%20community%20that%20a%20major%20change%20was%20underway%2C%20according%20to%20Zhou%20and%20other%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20think%20OpenAI%20is%20creating%20several%20smaller%20GPT-4%20models%20that%20act%20similarly%20to%20the%20large%20model%20but%20are%20less%20expensive%20to%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20approach%20is%20called%20a%20Mixture%20of%20Experts%2C%20or%20MOE%2C%20according%20to%20Zhou.%20The%20smaller%20expert%20models%20are%20each%20trained%20on%20different%20tasks%20and%20subject%20areas.%20There%20could%20be%20a%20mini%20biologist%20GPT-4%20and%20one%20for%20physics%2C%20chemistry%2C%20and%20so%20on.%20When%20a%20GPT-4%20user%20asks%20a%20question%2C%20the%20new%20system%20knows%20which%20expert%20model%20to%20send%20that%20query%20to.%20The%20new%20system%20might%20decide%20to%20send%20a%20query%20to%20two%20or%20more%20of%20these%20expert%20models%20just%20in%20case%2C%20and%20then%20mash%20up%20the%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20idea%20has%20been%20around%20for%20a%20while%20and%20it's%20a%20natural%20next%20step%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhou%20said.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZhou%20compared%20this%20situation%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BShip%20of%20Theseus%26quot%3B%20thought%20experiment%20where%20parts%20of%20the%20vessel%20were%20swapped%20out%20over%20time%2C%20begging%20the%20question%2C%20at%20what%20point%20does%20it%20become%20a%20whole%20new%20ship%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOpenAI%20is%20taking%20GPT-4%20and%20turning%20it%20into%20a%20fleet%20of%20smaller%20ships%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20my%20perspective%2C%20it's%20a%20new%20model.%20Some%20would%20say%20it's%20the%20same.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20asked%20OpenAI%20about%20all%20this%20on%20Tuesday.%20The%20company%2C%20partly%20owned%20by%20Microsoft%2C%20did%20not%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20week%2C%20several%20AI%20experts%20posted%20what%20they%20claimed%20were%20details%20of%20GPT-4's%20architecture%20on%20Twitter.%20Yam%20Peleg%2C%20a%20startup%20founder%2C%20tweeted%20that%20OpenAI%20was%20able%20to%20keep%20costs%20down%20by%20using%20a%20mixture%20of%20experts%20model%20with%2016%20experts.%20Semianalysis%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.semianalysis.com%2Fp%2Fgpt-4-architecture-infrastructure%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20inner%20workings%20of%20GPT-4%20this%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Hotz%2C%20a%20developer%20and%20hacker%2C%20described%20an%20%26quot%3Beight-way%20mixture%20model%26quot%3B%20for%20GPT-4%20during%20a%20recent%20podcast.%20Soumith%20Chintala%2C%20who%20co-founded%20the%20PyTorch%20open-source%20AI%20project%20at%20Meta%2C%20weighed%20in%20on%20Hotz's%20comments.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%20data-lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-conversation%20data-cards%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%E2%80%94Soumith%20Chintala%20(%40soumithchintala)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmims%2Fstatuses%2F1671267150101721090%5C%22%3EJune%2020%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20*%3Cstrong%3Econjecture%3C%2Fstrong%3E*%20that%20the%20speculations%20are%20roughly%20accurate%20but%20I%20don't%20have%20confirmation%2C%26quot%3B%20Oren%20Etzioni%2C%20founding%20CEO%20of%20the%20Allen%20Institute%20for%20AI%2C%20wrote%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Insider%20after%20seeing%20the%20leaks%20online%20this%20week.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20two%20main%20technical%20reasons%20to%20use%20an%20MOE%20approach%3A%20better%20generated%20responses%2C%20and%20cheaper%2C%20faster%20responses%2C%20he%20explained.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20'right'%20mixture%20will%20give%20you%20both%20but%20often%20there%20is%20a%20tradeoff%20between%20cost%20and%20quality%2C%26quot%3B%20Etzioni%20added.%20%26quot%3BIn%20this%20case%2C%20it%20seems%20anecdotally%20that%20OpenAI%20is%20sacrificing%20some%20quality%20for%20reduced%20cost.%20These%20models%20are%20very%20hard%20to%20evaluate%20(what%20constitutes%20a%20better%20response%3F%20In%20what%20cases%3F)%20so%20this%20isn't%20scientific%2C%20it's%20anecdotal.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpenAI%20wrote%20about%20the%20MOE%20approach%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenai.com%2Fresearch%2Ftechniques-for-training-large-neural-networks%5C%22%3E2022%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20co-authored%20by%20President%20Greg%20Brockman.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fabs%2F1701.06538%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMixture-of-Experts%20(MoE)%3C%2Fa%3E%20approach%2C%20only%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20network%20is%20used%20to%20compute%20the%20output%20for%20any%20one%20input.%20One%20example%20approach%20is%20to%20have%20many%20sets%20of%20weights%20and%20the%20network%20can%20choose%20which%20set%20to%20use%20via%20a%20gating%20mechanism%20at%20inference%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Brockman%20and%20his%20colleague%20Lilian%20Weng%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThis%20enables%20many%20more%20parameters%20without%20increased%20computation%20cost.%20Each%20set%20of%20weights%20is%20referred%20to%20as%20'experts%2C'%20in%20the%20hope%20that%20the%20network%20will%20learn%20to%20assign%20specialized%20computation%20and%20skills%20to%20each%20expert.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGPT-4's%20unnerving%20performance%20decline%20in%20recent%20weeks%20could%20well%20be%20related%20to%20this%20training%20and%20OpenAI%20rolling%20out%20this%20fleet%20of%20smaller%20expert%20GPT-4%20models%2C%20Zhou%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20users%20test%20it%2C%20we%20are%20going%20to%20ask%20so%20many%20different%20questions.%20It%20won't%20do%20as%20well%20but%20it's%20collecting%20data%20from%20us%20and%20it%20will%20improve%20and%20learn%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhou%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt4-ai-model-got-lazier-dumber-chatgpt-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689178035000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ae3ae194be880019f38606%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-gpt4-ai-model-got-lazier-dumber-chatgpt-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Users%20of%20OpenAI's%20GPT-4%20