n%20among%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarly%20in%20its%20statement%2C%20Amnesty%20notes%20the%20reprisals%20against%20activists%20and%20scholars%20who%20have%20spoken%20out%20against%20human%20rights%20abuses%20during%20the%20violence.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EInstances%20of%20this%20include%20a%20local%20court%20in%20Manipur%20summoning%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhyderabad-university-professor-two-kuki-activists-summoned-by-imphal-court-for-interviews-to-the-wire%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethree%20people%20who%20gave%20interviews%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20in%20which%20they%20demanded%20a%20separate%20administration%20for%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20Kuki%20community%20%E2%80%93%20and%20police%20filing%20an%20FIR%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-violence-fir-fact-finding-team%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eagainst%20a%20fact-finding%20committee%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20found%20the%20violence%20to%20be%20%E2%80%9Cstate-sponsored%E2%80%9D.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Manipur%20government%E2%80%99s%20home%20ministry%20has%20also%20asked%20police%20to%20file%20a%20case%20against%20Kuki%20student%20organisations%20for%20publishing%20a%20booklet%20on%20the%20violence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIndian%20authorities%20should%20meaningfully%20work%20together%20with%20civil%20society%20groups%20and%20community%20members%20of%20all%20ethnic%20groups%20to%20ensure%20that%20peace%20and%20security%20is%20restored%20in%20a%20human%20rights%20compliant%20manner.%20Victims%20of%20violence%20have%20a%20right%20to%20truth%2C%20accountability%2C%20and%20justice%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amnesty%20said%20in%20its%20statement.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERegarding%20reports%20of%20excesses%20by%20the%20state%20administration%2C%20Amnesty%20notes%20that%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-govt-issues-shoot-at-sight-orders-in-extreme-cases-amid-violence%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98shoot-on-sight%E2%80%99%20orders%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20promulgated%20by%20the%20government%20on%20May%204%20did%20not%20adhere%20to%20international%20legal%20norms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%20reads%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20the%20Manipur%20State%20government%20issued%20a%20%E2%80%98shoot-at-sight%E2%80%99%20order%20to%20all%20district%20magistrates%20in%20the%20state%20%E2%80%98in%20extreme%20cases%20after%20all%20forms%20of%20persuasion%2C%20warning%2C%20reasonable%20force%20have%20been%20exhausted%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98situation%20could%20not%20be%20controlled%E2%80%99.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CUnder%20international%20law%20and%20standards%2C%20law%20enforcement%20officials%20may%20only%20resort%20to%20such%20force%20when%20strictly%20unavoidable%20to%20protect%20against%20imminent%20threat%20of%20death%20or%20serious%20injury%2C%20which%20the%20order%20failed%20to%20clearly%20lay%20out%2C%20effectively%20permitting%20the%20deliberate%20and%20arbitrary%20killing%20of%20individuals%20who%20do%20not%20pose%20such%20a%20threat.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fmanipur-shoot-at-sight-order-principles%5C%22%3EManipur%3A%20Dissecting%20the%20Principles%20Associated%20With%20a%20%E2%80%98Shoot%20At%20Sight%E2%80%99%20Order%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmnesty%20also%20spoke%20to%20people%20who%20have%20been%20displaced%20by%20the%20violence%20in%20the%20state.%20According%20to%20fact-finding%20teams%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99s%20team%20of%20reporters%2C%20which%20visited%20the%20state%2C%20over%2060%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20displaced%20since%20the%20violence%20broke%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20survivor%20of%20the%20violence%20told%20the%20NGO%20that%20they%20and%20their%20family%20didn%E2%80%99t%20receive%20food%20or%20drinking%20water%20for%20two%20days%20at%20a%20relief%20camp%20and%20that%20their%20accommodation%20was%20%E2%80%9Cbasically%20a%20shed%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20%E2%80%9Cfacilities%20%5Bthat%20were%5D%20not%20hygienic.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20statement%20gives%20a%20large%20berth%20to%20discussing%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-manipur-high-court-internet%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eongoing%20internet%20shutdown%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20state%2C%20which%20has%20been%20in%20place%20for%20over%20two%20months%20now.%20In%20the%20following%20text%2C%20it%20highlights%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20international%20human%20rights%20law%2C%20as%20well%20as%20a%20judgement%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20are%20antithetical%20to%20the%20shutdown.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CStates%20parties%20must%20not%20block%20or%20hinder%20internet%20connectivity%20to%20curb%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20which%20is%20a%20right%20enshrined%20in%C2%A0%20the%20International%20Covenant%20on%20Civil%20and%20Political%20Rights%2C%20to%20which%20India%20is%20a%20state%20party%2C%20as%20well%20as%20in%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EAny%20restrictions%20on%20the%20operation%20of%20information%20dissemination%20systems%20must%20conform%20with%20the%20tests%20for%20restrictions%20on%20freedom%20of%20expression%E2%80%94notably%2C%20they%20should%20be%20legal%2C%20necessary%2C%20and%20proportionate.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20tests%20are%20laid%20down%20under%20international%20human%20rights%20law%20as%20well%20as%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20judgement%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalfreedomofexpression.columbia.edu%2Fcases%2Fbhasin-v-union-of-india%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAnuradha%20Bhasin%20vs.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20noted%20that%20the%20degree%20and%20scope%20of%20internet%20restrictions%20had%20to%20be%20proportionate%E2%80%9D.%20.%20Blanket%20%E2%80%93%20or%20total%20%E2%80%93%20cuts%20to%20internet%20access%20(or%20internet%20shutdowns)%20are%20inherently%20disproportionate%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%A6%3Ci%3E%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20also%20notes%20India%E2%80%99s%20status%20as%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ftech%2Findia-remains-internet-shutdown-capital-of-the-world-for-fifth-year-running-report%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eglobal%20leader%20in%20internet%20shutdowns%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20the%20last%20five%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmnesty%20International%20asked%20Indian%20authorities%20to%20immediately%20restore%20internet%20access%20in%20the%20state%20and%20work%20with%20civil%20society%20groups%20and%20community%20members%20of%20all%20ethnic%20groups%20to%20ensure%20that%20peace%20and%20security%20are%20restored.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CVictims%20of%20violence%20have%20a%20right%20to%20truth%2C%20accountability%2C%20and%20justice.%20Police%20excesses%20and%20reports%20of%20police%20bias%20need%20to%20be%20immediately%2C%20independently%2C%20and%20impartially%20investigated.%20Indian%20state%20authorities%20should%20coordinate%20with%20each%20other%20and%20with%20local%20groups%20to%20ensure%20that%20necessities%20of%20adequate%20and%20sanitary%20housing%2C%20safety%2C%20clothing%2C%20clean%20water%2C%20nutrition%20and%20health%20care%20is%20accessible%20to%20all%20%5Binternally%20displaced%20persons%5D%20who%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20flee.%20Authorities%20must%20facilitate%20the%20IDPs%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20voluntarily%20return%20to%20their%20homes%20and%20rebuild%20their%20lives%20by%20ensuring%20safe%20rehabilitation%20and%2For%20resettlement%2C%E2%80%9D%20Amnesty%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NGO%20has%20also%20been%20targeted%20by%20Indian%20authorities.%20Its%20Bangalore%20and%20Delhi%20offices%20were%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Famnesty-india-cbi-raids-fcra%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eraided%20by%20the%20CBI%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%202019%20and%20it%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Famnesty-international-india-shuts-down-inquiries-investigating-agencies-ed-cbi%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eforced%20to%20shut%20down%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20its%20India%20operations%20in%202020%20after%20its%20accounts%20were%20frozen.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Enforcement%20Directorate%2C%20a%20federal%20financial%20crimes%20agency%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fenforcement-directorate-amnesty-india-money-laundering%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efiled%20a%20money%20laundering%20chargesheet%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20against%20its%20India%20division%20last%20year%20and%20fined%20it%20Rs%2051%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689176712000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F12081122%2FScreenshot-2023-06-12-at-8.08.47-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Famnesty-alarm-manipur-violence-peace%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20human%20rights%20NGO%20released%20a%20public%20statement%20in%20which%20it%20takes%20note%20of%20reprisals%20against%20scholars%20and%20activists%20and%20allegations%20of%20police%20excesses.%20The%20statement%20also%20features%20conversations%20with%20victims%20of%20Manipur's%20violence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%