3Ereport%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20(ADR).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20titled%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAnalysis%20of%20Donations%20to%20Registered%20Recognised%20Political%20Parties%20from%20FY%202016-17%20to%20FY%202021-22%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20analyses%20donations%20to%20the%2031%20recognised%20political%20parties%20%E2%80%93%20seven%20national%20and%2024%20regional%20parties%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20between%20financial%20year%20(FY)%202016-17%20and%20FY%202021-22.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20six-year%20period%20is%20significant%20because%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdea.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FElectoral%2520Bonds_Press%2520RELEASE_2-1-2018.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EElectoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20was%20introduced%20in%202018%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20electoral%20funding%2C%20while%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.civilaviation.gov.in%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FMoL%2526amp%253BJ%2520%2528Legislative%2520Deptt%2529%2520The%2520Finance%2520Act%2520.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EFinance%20Act%202017%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20removed%20the%20earlier%20limit%20of%207.5%25%20of%20a%20company%E2%80%99s%20average%20three-year%20net%20profit%20for%20political%20donations.%20A%20company%20is%20also%20not%20required%20to%20name%20the%20political%20parties%20to%20which%20such%20contributions%20are%20made%20under%20the%202018%20scheme.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202019%20general%20elections%20also%20took%20place%20during%20this%20period%20along%20with%20a%20total%20of%2045%20state%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20the%20total%20donations%20declared%20by%20the%20seven%20national%20parties%20and%2024%20regional%20parties%20in%20this%20period%20were%20Rs%2013%2C190.68%20crore%20(80%25%20of%20total%20donations)%20and%20Rs%203%2C246.95%20crore%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENational%20parties%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20total%20donations%20declared%20by%20BJP%20are%20more%20than%20three%20times%20the%20total%20donations%20declared%20by%20all%20other%20national%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20during%20this%20six-year%20period%2C%20more%20than%2052%25%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20total%20donations%20came%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%205271.97%20crore.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Congress%20declared%20the%20second-highest%20donations%20from%20bonds%20at%20Rs%20952.29%20crore%20which%20accounts%20for%20just%20over%2060%25%20of%20its%20total%20donations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20followed%20by%20the%20All%20India%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(AITC)%2C%20which%20declared%20Rs%20767.88%20crore%2C%20accounting%20for%20almost%2093%25%20of%20its%20total%20donations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ERegional%20parties%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20regional%20parties%2C%20almost%2090%25%C2%A0%20of%20the%20Biju%20Janata%20Dal%20(BJD)%E2%80%99s%20total%20donations%20worth%20Rs%20622%20crore%20came%20from%20electoral%20bonds.%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmong%20regional%20parties%2C%20DMK%20declared%20the%20second%20highest%20donations%20from%20bonds%2C%20at%20Rs%20431.50%20crore%20(90.7%25%20of%20its%20total%20donations).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20was%20followed%20by%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%2C%20which%20declared%20Rs%20383.65%20crore%20accounting%20for%2080.45%25%20of%20its%20total%20donations%20and%20YSRCP%2C%20which%20declared%20Rs%20330.44%20crore%20that%20made%20up%2072.43%25%20of%20its%20total%20donations.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20the%20corporate%20donations%20declared%20by%20the%20BJP%20are%20at%20least%20three-four%20times%20more%20than%20the%20total%20corporate%20donations%20of%20all%20other%20national%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20in%20FY%202017-18%2C%20it%20was%20more%20than%2018%20times%20that%20of%20all%20other%20national%20parties.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDirect%20corporate%20donations%20declared%20by%20regional%20parties%20also%20increased%20by%20152%25%20in%20this%20period.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20party%20which%20has%20no%20declared%20corporate%20donations%20is%20the%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20while%20the%20Communist%20Party%20of%20India%20declared%20receiving%20zero%20corporate%20donations%20from%20FY%202018-19%20to%20FY%202021-22%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20added%20that%20the%20highest%20donations%20were%20received%20during%202019%2C%20when%20general%20elections%20were%20held.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20FY%202019-20%2C%20donations%20worth%20Rs%204%2C863.5%20crore%20were%20received%20in%20the%20form%20of%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20followed%20by%20Rs%204%2C041.4%20crore%20in%20FY%202018-19%20and%20Rs%203826.56%20crore%20in%20FY%202021-22.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20has%20been%20criticised%20for%20its%20lack%20of%20transparency.%20Petitions%20challenging%20its%20constitutionality%20are%20pending%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20January%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20categorised%20the%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20into%20three%20sets%20to%20hear%20them%20separately.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThese%20include%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%3B%20whether%20political%20parties%20should%20be%20brought%20within%20the%20purview%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20Act%2C%202005%3B%20and%20the%20challenge%20to%20the%20amendment%20to%20the%20Foreign%20Contribution%20Regulation%20Act%2C%202010%20through%20the%20Finance%20Act%20of%202016%20and%202018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689168666000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F12184145%2Frupee-4395462_1280.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-donations-electoral-bonds-thrice-other-parties-adr%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20analysed%20donations%20received%20by%20political%20parties%20between%202016-17%20and%202021-22%2C%20a%20crucial%20period%20in%20which%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20was%20introduced%20and%20the%20removal%20of%20a%20limit%20on%20political%20donations%20by%20companies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-donations-electoral-bonds-thrice-other-parties-adr%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Igniting%20Ideas%20for%20Impact%3A%20Audiobook%20on%20How%20India%E2%80%99s%20Brilliant%20Minds%20Are%20Transforming%20Millions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20has%20been%20published%20in%20partnership%20with%20Accenture%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%2090s%2C%20Geetha%20Manjunath%20was%20part%20of%20a%20team%20that%20helped%20design%20the%20first%20Indian%20commercial%20supercomputer.%20This%2C%20she%20recalls%2C%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20times%20she%20realised%20she%20needed%20to%20work%20twice%20as%20hard%20%E2%80%94%20and%20show%20double%20the%20results%20%E2%80%94%20to%20be%20treated%20at%20par%20with%20her%20male%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%20the%20NIRAMAI%20founder%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F303740%