ver%2010%20million%20times%20on%20TikTok%20and%20had%20thousands%20of%20comments%20from%20viewers%20from%20across%20the%20globe.%20According%20to%20a%20report%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news.com.au%2Ftechnology%2Fscience%2Fanimals%2Fterrifying-creature-from-hell-is-identified%2Fnews-story%2Fbc99bd0d18634bd38dd42ec8341d6d88%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENews.com.au%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20blue-greyish%20creature%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20half-stick%20insect%2C%20half%20scorpion.%20It%20also%20has%20wings%20and%20a%20tail%20that%20goes%20up%20and%20down%20in%20a%20stabbing%20motion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESee%20the%20video%20here%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FcwjJv4aQ9aE%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22469%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22creature%20from%20hell%3F%20laverton%20western%20Australia%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22833%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Australian%20man%20claimed%20that%20the%20creature%20was%20spotted%20in%20the%20outback%20town%20of%20Laverton%2C%20Western%20Australia-%20about%20a%2010-hour%20drive%20from%20Perth.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20video%20amassed%20an%20array%20of%20reactions%20and%20a%20section%20of%20users%20said%20that%20they%20were%20%26quot%3Bterrified%26quot%3B%20to%20come%20to%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAustralia%20looks%20gorgeous%20but%20the%20insects%20carry%20guns%20and%20smoke%20cigars%2C%20never%20going%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20user%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYeah%2C%20Nah%2C%20just%20another%20reason%20to%20never%20go%20to%20Australia%2C%26quot%3B%20another%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToo%20many%20spicy%20scorpions%2C%20fan%2C%20pencil%20things%20like%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20people%20from%20Australia%20said%20that%20they%20hope%20that%20the%20creepy%20crawly%20remains%20in%20the%20remote%20part%20of%20Western%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSaw%20one%20of%20these%20in%20Woodford%2C%20Queensland%2C%20a%20few%20days%20ago%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20definitely%20not%20something%20I%20wanted%20in%20my%20house!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENews.com.au%3C%2Fem%3E%20spoke%20to%20a%20Perth-based%20entomologist%20to%20identify%20the%20insect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20walking%20stick%20insect%2C%20in%20the%20family%20Phasmatidae%2C%26quot%3B%20Nikolai%20Tatarnic%2C%20Curator%20of%20Entomology%20at%20the%20Western%20Australian%20Museum%20told%20the%20media%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhile%20most%20people%20are%20aware%20of%20their%20camouflage%20(i.e.%20looking%20like%20a%20stick)%2C%20some%20species%20also%20engage%20in%20threat%20or%20startle%20displays%20(also%20called%20'deimatic%20behaviour')%20to%20ward%20off%20potential%20predators.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20the%20insect%20in%20the%20clip%20is%20the%20genus%20Paronchestus%2C%20probably%20P.%20cornutus%2C%20as%20it%20closely%20resembles%20a%20specimen%20in%20our%20collection%2C%20which%20was%20collected%20from%20Laverton.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPhasmids%20are%20herbivores%20and%20are%20not%20venomous.%20The%20terrifying%20display%20in%20the%20video%20is%20all%20a%20ruse%2C%20but%20it%20clearly%20works.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPhasmids%20are%20found%20all%20across%20Australia%2C%20but%20because%20of%20their%20amazing%20camouflage%2C%20they%20mostly%20go%20unseen%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Tatarnic%20told%20the%20media%20outlet.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689168300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-07%2Fpoje0fco_the-video-was-viewed-over-10-million-times-on-tiktok_625x300_12_July_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fchilling-video-of-creature-from-hell-stuns-internet-4201154%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20insect%20in%20the%20clip%20is%20the%20genus%20Paronchestus%2C%20pr