%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22India%20Votes%20in%20Favour%20of%20UNHRC%20Resolution%20Against%20'Religious%20Hatred'%20After%20Sweden%20Quran%20Burning%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F23142706%2F5553604787_a38f04d388_k1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20United%20Nations%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20has%20adopted%20the%20draft%20resolution%20presented%20by%20Pakistan%20on%20countering%20religious%20hatred%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20Quran-burning%20episode%20in%20Sweden%2C%20with%20India%20voting%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-0%5C%22%3EThe%20draft%20resolution%20L.23%20was%20orally%20revised%20once%20tabled.%20It%20is%20titled%20%E2%80%98Countering%20religious%20hatred%20constituting%20incitement%20to%20discrimination%2C%20hostility%20or%20violence%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-0%5C%22%3EIn%20late%20June%2C%20a%20man%20had%20torn%20and%20burned%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20Quran%20outside%20Swedish%20capital%20Stockholm%E2%80%99s%20central%20mosque.%20He%20was%20charged%20with%20agitating%20against%20an%20ethnic%20or%20national%20group%20by%20Swedish%20police%2C%20Reuters%20had%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-0%5C%22%3EThe%20US%2C%20and%20crucially%20Turkey%2C%20whose%20backing%20Sweden%20seeks%20in%20its%20bid%20to%20join%20NATO%2C%20had%20both%20criticised%20the%20incident.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-1%5C%22%3EThe%20Organisation%20of%20Islamic%20Cooperation%2C%20comprising%2057%20countries%2C%20had%20called%20the%20incident%20%E2%80%9Coffensive%2C%20disrespectful%20and%20a%20clear%20act%20of%20provocation%E2%80%9D%20that%20incites%20hatred%20and%20constitutes%20a%20human%20rights%20violation%2C%20according%20to%20another%20Reuters%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-1%5C%22%3EPakistan%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20OIC%2C%20had%20presented%20the%20draft%20resolution%20which%20condemned%20%E2%80%9Crecurring%20acts%20of%20the%20public%20burning%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20Quran%20in%20%E2%80%9Csome%20European%20and%20other%20countries%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-1%5C%22%3EDespite%20Western%20diplomats%E2%80%99%20opposition%20to%20the%20resolution%2C%2019%20OIC%20countries%20are%20voting%20members%20of%20the%2047-member%20human%20rights%20council%2C%20and%20other%20states%20such%20as%20China%20had%20aligned%20with%20their%20draft%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-1%5C%22%3EAmong%20the%2012%20countries%20that%20voted%20against%20this%20resolution%20are%20the%20US%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20France%20Belgium%2C%20Germany%2C%20Romania%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20Costa%20Rica%20and%20Finland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20data-testid%3D%5C%22paragraph-1%5C%22%3ENepal%2C%20Paraguay%2C%20Georgia%2C%20Benin%2C%20Chile%2C%20Honduras%2C%20and%20Mexico%20abstained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty-eight%20countries%2C%20including%20India%2C%20China%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20Ukraine%2C%20voted%20for%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20did%20not%20explain%20its%20vote%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20but%20it%20made%20a%20statement%20during%20the%20debate%20on%20July%2011.%20However%2C%20the%20statement%20made%20no%20explicit%20reference%20to%20the%20Sweden%20incident.%20India%20has%20also%20not%20issued%20any%20separate%20reaction%20to%20the%20Quran%20burning%2C%20and%20there%20was%20no%20direct%20condemnation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20stated%20that%20there%20was%20an%20increase%20in%20%E2%80%9Cphobias%E2%80%9D%20against%20all%20religions%20and%20did%20not%20mention%20Islam%20by%20name.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20various%20regions%20of%20the%20world%2C%20we%20have%20witnessed%20defacement%20and%20destruction%20of%20temples%20and%20idols%2C%20glorification%20of%20desecration%20of%20idols%2C%20violation%20of%20%3Cem%3Egurudwara%3C%2Fem%3E%20premises%2C%20massacre%20of%20Sikh%20pilgrims%20and%20numerous%20other%20acts%20of%20religious%20intolerance.%20There%20is%20a%20need%20for%20the%20international%20community%20to%20recognize%20the%20instances%20of%20intolerance%2C%20prejudice%2C%20phobia%2C%20and%20violence%20against%20followers%20of%20all%20religions%20and%20work%20together%20to%20eliminate%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20Indian%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20India%20claimed%20that%20its%20tolerance%20was%20based%20on%20its%20%E2%80%9Ccivilizational%20ethos%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20guarantees%20inscribed%20in%20the%20Constitution.%20%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20civilizational%20emphasis%20on%20%3Cem%3EVasudhaiva%20Kutumbakam%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20is%20%E2%80%98the%20World%20is%20one%20family%E2%80%99%20provides%20the%20basis%20for%20the%20elimination%20of%20all%20kinds%20of%20religious%20hatred%2C%20discrimination%20and%20intolerance%20directed%20against%20followers%20of%20all%20religions.%C2%A0%20It%20is%20high%20time%20that%20all%20members%20States%20join%20hands%20to%20build%20a%20culture%20of%20equal%20respect%20for%20all%20religions%20and%20their%20peaceful%20coexistence%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20Indian%20representative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20vote%2C%20US%20Michele%20Taylor%20said%20that%20if%20there%20had%20been%20more%20time%2C%20a%20consensus%20could%20have%20been%20reached.%20%E2%80%9CUnfortunately%20our%20concerns%20were%20not%20taken%20seriously%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20as%20per%20%3Cem%3EAFP%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20truly%20heartbroken%20that%20this%20council%20was%20unable%20to%20speak%20with%20a%20unanimous%20voice%20today%20in%20condemning%20what%20we%20all%20agree%20are%20deplorable%20acts%20of%20anti-Muslim%20hatred%20while%20also%20respecting%20freedom%20of%20expression.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%E2%80%99s%20Permanent%20Representative%20to%20the%20U.N.%20in%20Geneva%2C%20Khalil%20Hasmi%2C%20accused%20the%20West%20of%20%E2%80%9Clip%20service%E2%80%9D%20to%20their%20commitment%20to%20prevent%20religious%20hatred.%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CThe%20opposition%20of%20a%20few%20in%20the%20room%20has%20emanated%20from%20their%20unwillingness%20to%20condemn%20the%20public%20desecration%20of%20the%20Holy%20Koran%20or%20any%20other%20religious%20book%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%2C%20as%20quoted%20by%20%3Cem%3EReuters%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20lack%20political%2C%20legal%20and%20moral%20courage%20to%20condemn%20this%20act%2C%20and%20it%20was%20the%20minimum%20that%20the%20Council%20could%20have%20expected%20from%20them%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Hashmi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%F0%9F%94%B4BREAKING%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FUN%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%40UN%3C%2Fa%3E%F0%9F%87%BA%F0%9F%87%B3%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20adopted%20draft%20resolution%20L.23%20(as%20orally%20revised)%20entitled%20%26quot%3BCountering%20religious%20hatred%20constituting%20incitement%20to%20discrimination%2C%20hostility%20or%20violence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFull%20results%20of%20the%C2%A0vote%C2%A0at%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FHRC53%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23HRC53%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%A4%B5%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FRqQM7m1dBP%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FRqQM7m1dBP%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20United%20Nations%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20%F0%9F%93%8D%20%23HRC53%20(%40UN_HRC)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FUN_HRC%2Fstatus%2F1679044013746274304%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2012%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20This%20article%20was%20updated%20after%20it%20was%20published%20with%2